# Benchmark F reference data — materialised on demand by
# download_references.py. None of it should be committed:
#
#   * Sizes vary (some files are 10s of MB)
#   * Licences vary (some have attribution requirements)
#   * The build recipes in this directory are the authoritative source
#     of truth — anyone can reproduce the references with `make references`

# ── Tabular references (DE tables, gene counts, MultiQC summaries) ──
*.tsv
*.csv
*.txt

# ── Genomic interval / annotation files ─────────────────────────────
*.bed
*.bed.gz
*.narrowPeak
*.broadPeak
*.gappedPeak
*.bedGraph
*.bigwig
*.bw
*.gtf
*.gff
*.gff3

# ── Variant calls + indexes ─────────────────────────────────────────
*.vcf
*.vcf.gz
*.tbi
*.csi

# ── Sequence + alignment files (in case anyone caches them here) ────
*.fa
*.fa.gz
*.fasta
*.fasta.gz
*.fai
*.dict
*.bam
*.bam.bai
*.bai
*.cram
*.crai
*.fastq
*.fastq.gz
*.fq
*.fq.gz

# ── Compressed downloads + spreadsheets + temp files ────────────────
*.gz
*.bz2
*.zip
*.tar
*.xlsx
*.xls
*.part

# ── R / RStudio cruft ───────────────────────────────────────────────
.Rhistory
.Rapp.history
.RData
.Ruserdata
.Rproj.user/
omnipathr-log/
*-log/

# ── Python cache ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
__pycache__/
*.pyc

# ── Always keep the orchestrators, recipes, and docs ────────────────
!download_references.py
!install_r_deps.R
!make_reference_*.R
!macs_txt_to_bed.py
!counts_tsv_to_bed.py
!subset_giab_chr20.sh
!README.md
!.gitignore
